 Lagos State Government has warned against indiscriminate dumping of refuse in the sprawling city, pointing out that it has strengthened its environmental enforcement law to deal with environmental offenders across the state. May 8, 2018 In "Homes & Property" The Lagos State Government on Wednesday arrested a total of 24 persons including cart pushers, street traders and some residents for dumping waste on road medians and canals contrary to the Environmental Sanitation Laws of the State. January 24, 2018 In "Metro" The Lagos State Government has directed that officers from Lagos State Environmental Sanitation Corps (LAGESC), who are reportedly involved in a street combat in Ilasamaja area of Isolo, putting the state government in bad light, should be brought to book by facing consequences of their actions. October 13, 2018 In "News"